b10_fight_dialoge_0: §c Free at last! For you... it's time to die!
b10_fight_dialoge_1: I won't let you get away!
b10_fight_dialoge_10: The spores are blocking my portals, §epush them away §ffrom the portals! Don't let two spores touch!
b10_fight_dialoge_11: It is attracting the spores, §cDon't let the spores touch§f!
b10_fight_dialoge_12: §c Okay, §oheroes§c, you're very entertaining... Let's play a little game!
b10_fight_dialoge_13: Focus! Don't fall for his tricks!
b10_fight_dialoge_14: §c So, the big §oheroes§c think they know how to play? I'll show you!
b10_fight_dialoge_20: Kill all the sentinels before is too late!
b10_fight_dialoge_21: §c The curtain rises again... on this delightful little game!
b10_fight_dialoge_22: And this will be the final act!
b10_fight_dialoge_27: §c No one is coming to save you, Eo'Thar. You're next!
b10_fight_dialoge_29: §c Now I know, without any doubt, that you are worthy of the destiny Thar Kroo wrote for you.
b10_fight_dialoge_30: §c§o "The liberators of §e§oAphofis§c§o, the saviors of the galaxy."
b10_fight_dialoge_31: §c Though I would call you something else... the liberators of the §eNightmare§c!
b10_fight_dialoge_32: §c For now, I shall withdraw. Prolonging this battle would no longer benefit me.
b10_fight_dialoge_33: §c I know your power now... and the board is almost prepared.
b10_fight_dialoge_34: §c When every piece falls into place, you will understand the price of your actions.
b10_fight_dialoge_37: He's gone... and this §eplace§f is getting §eunstable§f. I'll §eget you out§f!
b10_fight_dialoge_38: I'll stay behind and search for him.
b10_fight_dialoge_39: I don't have much time left... Don't let him §cmanifest in reality again§f!
b10_fight_dialoge_4: I've placed portals! Cross them to dodge the dark clock hands.
b10_fight_dialoge_6: §c Poor Eo'Thar! Your portal magic is weakening!
b10_fight_dialoge_7: §c This is what a nightmare looks like.

§rI can foresee his abilities: 
§4§l<!> WARNING <!> §r§cThis boss is tough. You might need to come back later with better gear.
b10_info_dialog_2: §rI don't like you, but he's right. I can't hold him back much longer. I need your help to defeat him. Be sure to bring §aarea-of-effect§f and §aknockback§f weapons.
b10_info_dialog_20:
§rAre you sure you want to start the fight? 
§4§l<!> WARNING <!> §r§cThis boss is tough. You might need to come back later with better gear.
b10_info_dialog_22: I can lend you this, for now.
b10_info_dialog_3: §e▶ §7I don't understand what this place is. Who are you?
b10_info_dialog_5: §rAs you probably know, I was the warden of the Tower of Time, a sacred place where the energy used by the lineage of Bani to protect time converges. Thanks to that bond, I was able to take refuge in Aphofis's dreams the day the Conqueror broke in. Since then, he has tried to subjugate Aphofis using the power of the tower, and a nightmare has been growing in her mind.
b10_info_dialog_6: §e▶ §7So we're inside Aphofis's dreams? Facing her nightmares?
b10_info_dialog_7: §rYes, and I had the situation more or less under control... until you appeared. Your intrusion almost allowed Maraw'Thar to manifest in the real plane, though it was weak there, and you managed to contain it.
b10_info_dialog_8: §e▶ §7Don't worry! I can defeat it again!
b10_info_dialog_9: §rHere it's far stronger. Ever since your arrival I've barely been able to hold it back. And whether I like it or not, I can't face it alone. If this nightmare comes true, we'll be in deep trouble, so we'll have to fight together.
b10_info_hover_11:
§c§lClock Hands (§r§c☠§c§l deadly)

§7§o(Third-person view is §b§ohighly recommended§7§o (F5) since it is necessary to have §e§overy good control§7§o over what is happening in the arena)§f 

§r§fThe §earena is a clock§r§f, and Maraw'thar will summon several §eprofane clock hands§r that will rotate across the arena. 

They cannot be jumped over, and touching one will inflict §cdamage§f that will §ctriple ☠§f every time you touch a hand again.

§4§l<!> §cThe damage from this ability §epierces §cany §eresistance §cor §eimmunity§c.
b10_info_hover_12:
§6§lDevouring Onslaught (! dangerous)

§r§fMaraw'Thar will §erepeatedly charge§f at a random player from a random angle, §ceven from behind§f. Dodge it by sidestepping. 

The damage §cdoubles§f each time it hits you, but the damage stack resets after a short time.
b10_info_hover_13:
§6§lOcular Swarm (! dangerous)

§r§fMaraw'Thar §edisappears momentarily§f and fills the entire arena floor with eyes. After a few seconds, these §cexplode§f, dealing damage that §cdoubles§f each time you are hit.

§r§fStand on the eyes that are §aclosed§f to avoid taking damage.
b10_info_hover_14:
§b§lEo'Thar Portals (! Important)

§r§fEo'Thar places §epairs of linked portals§f across the arena to help you dodge the rotating §cclock hands§f. Each portal has an arrow nearby that §bindicates§f which portal it is connected to. You can enter through one and §aexit§f through its partner instantly.
b10_info_hover_15:
§c§lGanglionic Spores (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§r§fMaraw'Thar will vilely §cvomit a spore§f onto an §bEo'Thar portal§f where there isn't already §cone§f nearby. The spore will §cblock ONLY the entrance§f of all nearby §bportals§f

§r§fSince §bEo'Thar's portals§f work in §bpairs§f, you can still §aexit§f through the linked portal even if its partner is §cblocked§f. 

§r§fYou §ccannot kill§f a spore, only §apush it away§f. Push spores using bows with §apunch§f or weapons with §aknockback§f to keep them away from the portals. However, spores are §eslightly attracted§f back toward the §bportals§f over time.

§r§fIf two spores get too close to each other, they will §cexplode§f, dealing §cmassive damage ☠§r every second. §cDon't let them merge!§f
b10_info_hover_17:
§c§lDark Ring (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§r§fMaraw'Thar summons a §cdark ring§f that either §cexpands§f or §cretracts§f from a fixed position. Touching it deals the same damage as being hit by a §cclock hand§f.

§r§fUse §bEo'Thar's portals§f to dodge these deadly rings.
b10_info_hover_18:
§c§lStalking Sentinels (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§r§fAt the end of the interphase, Maraw'Thar summons §c12 sentinels§f, and a short §ccountdown§f begins. If the timer expires and they aren't all killed, §ceveryone will die instantly§f.

§r§fBring plenty of §aarea-of-effect damage§f to clear them in time!
b10_info_hover_19:
§c§lAttract Spores (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§r§fMaraw'Thar moves to the §ccenter of the arena§f and begins to §cattract all spores§f toward himself for a few seconds. When the effect ends, §call spores will disappear§f.

§r§fRemember: if two spores §ctouch§f during the pull, they will §cexplode§f, dealing §cmassive lethal damage ☠§f every second. §cKeep them apart at all costs!§f
b10_ini_dialoge_1: §c Oh Eo'Thar! Look who showed up!
b10_ini_dialoge_10:
Damn you! 
§o§7Right-click to speak with Eo'thar!
b10_ini_dialoge_4: Get out of here, you've already caused enough trouble!
b10_ini_dialoge_5: §c This prison of yours won't hold me much longer, Eo'thar.
b10_ini_dialoge_6: §c Do you not want these §oheroes§r§c to see how I crush your last delusions of consciousness?
b10_ini_dialoge_8: §c Come on, Eo'thar... We both know what's going to happen.
b10_ini_dialoge_9: §c You're cornered. You're alone. Stop delaying the inevitable.
b11_text_10: §e §lYOU§e... you are the ones who broke me!
b11_text_13: §e I no longer know who I am...
b11_text_14: §e Have you come for my cosmic core? TO EXTEND MY TORMENT?
b11_text_15: §e §lMARAW'THAR§e HAS SHOWN ME... THE TRUTH, CONQUEROR...
b11_text_16: §e It is already inside your mind as well...
b11_text_17: §e Let me show you the truth...
b11_text_18: Madness has consumed her, heroes... We must put an end to her suffering.
b11_text_19: Speak to me. I stand before the Queen!
b11_text_20: Once a §emajestic§f and revered being, now just an §eabject aberration§f that mistakes us for the Conqueror. We must free it from its torment to recover the §ecosmic core§f.
b11_text_21: §e▶ §7How can I §ebeat§7 The Queen of the Hive?
b11_text_22: §e▶ §7How did she end up like this?
b11_text_23: The battle has three phases, and two interphases. She only §ereceives damage§f on the §ehead§f. These are her abilities:
b11_text_26:
§b§lBloodhoney Homeostasis (! Important)

§fThe queen always keeps §e4 Honey Mummies§f in the arena. Killing one §eimmediately§f spawns §eanother§f.
Mummies are §eimmobile§f and deal §3no damage§f. After §c§l4 hits§f, they §cdie§f.

If §aYOU§f land the §afinal hit§f, the mummy §adies safely§f. 
If the §cQUEEN§f lands the §cfinal hit§f, it becomes a §cBloodhoney Spawn§f that will §cchase§f and §cattack§f you. If the §cBloodhoney Spawn§f is not eliminated within §e10 seconds§f, it will enrage, §clethally ☠§f boosting its damage! 

Mummies show hit progress on their health bar and §cglow red§f when §eone hit away§f.

The mummies also drop §efood§f, §earrows§f, and §eweapons§f.

§b§lTip:§f finish the mummies when they are at one hit remaining, to save time.
b11_text_28:
§e§lBloodhoney Bolt

§fAfter a §eshort cast§f, the queen §cspits§f a bloodhoney bolt §c§lforward§f and §c§ltoward§f each §6honey mummy§f and §cBloodhoney Spawn§f, damaging both players and §emummies§f.

§b§lTip:§f step out of the boss's front and avoid standing between the boss and a mummy.
b11_text_30:
§6§lHivebreaker (! dangerous)

§fThe boss will perform a §esequence§f of these two attacks:

§6§lGround Slam:§f The queen smashes one §centire half§f of the arena, dealing damage to §eplayers§f and §emummies§f.

§6§lRadial Slam:§f The queen spins in place, dealing damage to all nearby §eplayers§f and §emummies§f in a circular area.
b11_text_32:
§e§lAssault from Below

§fThe queen §edives§f underground and repeatedly §eleaps§f at players, §bincreasing speed§f each time.

This attack does not damage mummies, only players.
b11_text_34:
§c§lDeranging Scream (§r§c☠§c§l deadly)

§fThe queen inhales briefly, then unleashes a §eterrifying scream§f that §edeals damage§f every 1.5 seconds for 4.5 seconds §7(§e3 ticks§7 in total)§f to all §eplayers§f and §emummies§f in her line of sight.

§b§lTip:§f Keep a §emummy§f at §e4 HP§f and §chide behind§f it when the scream occurs. If the mummy has 3 HP or less, it will die mid-scream, leaving you §cexposed§f.
b11_text_36:
§6§lEnrage (! dangerous)

§fDuring the §efinal phase §7§o(phase 3)§f, the queen becomes §cenraged§f and performs §e§lBloodhoney Bolt§f and §6§lGround Slam §bfaster§f.
b11_text_37: The Conqueror is searching for a powerful being to steal its strength and carry out his crusade. It seems this was his first test subject, a failed one. The queen is trapped in a deep nightmare she cannot escape from, and we are her only way out.
b11_text_40: §cI am so sorry... you deserved better... you poor soul...
b11_text_41: §cAnd I am sorry for you as well, my champions, for having to witness this.
b11_text_42: §cSuch a kind soul with a great heart... It is painful to see what they... turned her into...
b11_text_43: §cI fear the Conqueror's next target may be the cosmic serpent §eBANI§c...
b11_text_50: §eJoin me in my nightmare of blood and honey.
b11_text_54: §eYou will feel every drop of my suffering!
b11_text_55: §eThis is all your fault! I was not always like this...
b11_text_57: The Queen has §cenraged§f, now her attacks go §efaster§f!
b11_text_60: Greetings, heroes. As you can see, I can manifest §eechoes of myself§f whenever there is §esomething important§f you need §eto know§f.
b11_text_62:
The §ehoney§f in this place still retains the Queen's original power. §eStepping on it§f grants §bspeed I§f, §ehaste I§f, §6resistance I§f, and §6fire resistance§f for §350 seconds§f, and also §acleanses poison§f.

This is very useful, as enemies in this area wield §6fire§f and §apoison-based§f abilities.
b11_text_64: Since the §eConqueror experimented§f on the Queen to §esteal her power§f, she §elost herself§f within her own mind. The entire hive followed the same fate. Since then, they have been nothing more than disturbed insects, without direction or purpose.
b11_text_66: Stepping on §ehoney§f removes §apoison§f and grants §6resistance§f, §6fire resistance§f, §bspeed§f, and §ehaste§f for 50 seconds.
b11_text_67: The §ehoney§f is §esticky§f, you might be able to use it to §eslide down safely§f!
b11_text_68: The §ehoney§f is §esticky§f, you might be able to use it to §eslide down safely§f!
b11_text_71: §6§l/§f§l9§f Maldini's cats. Come back to him when you have them §eall§f to receive your §ereward§f!
b11_text_73: Well done! You have rescued §a§lall §fMaldini's cats. Come back to him to receive your §ereward§f!
b11_text_74: §fThis cat belongs to §eMaldini§f. Talk to §ehim§f at the §6first intersection§f to learn what to do with the cat.
b11_text_9: §e The Conqueror? Ectron? You are the Conqueror... You did this to me... I can't endure it...
b9_dialogo_1: You arrived too late... I couldn't hold him back any longer...
b9_dialogo_10: §c That is what I am, and the only thing you will know from now on.
b9_dialogo_12: §c Allow me to demonstrate to you what The Conqueror could not. HAHA-awhahahHAHa
b9_dialogo_13: I just can't believe my eyes. Talk to me now!
b9_dialogo_14: §cHeroes... be the first to witness my true power!
b9_dialogo_15: §cYou will burn in Bani's dark flames!
b9_dialogo_16: §cThar Kroo never understood the true nature of his powers! I do!
b9_dialogo_17: §cYour downfall will mark the beginning of a new era of suffering and terror!
b9_dialogo_2: §c This is the beginning and the end, heroes.
b9_dialogo_20:
All players §cmust equip§f the §dGauntlet of Atacrom§f in their §eoff-hand§f! 

§7§o(If you've lost it, return to the forge and speak with Atacrom to obtain a new one.)
b9_dialogo_4: §c Your victory over The Conqueror has only led you to the worst possible fate.
b9_dialogo_5: §c Ever since I've been freed from his yoke, my power flows without limit.
b9_dialogo_6: §c How naive of §eThar Kroo§c and §eEctron§c to think they could harness my power endlessly.
b9_dialogo_7: §c Good thing the §oheroes§c arrived to set me free!
b9_dialogo_8: §c I am the Stygian Ash, the dark fire of §eBani§c, the true power of the Conqueror.
b9_dialogo_9: §c A force of nature, unstoppable, born of torture and suffering.
b9_dialogo_victoria_12: With it defeated, this realm is collapsing. This nightmare cannot sustain itself any longer.
b9_dialogo_victoria_13: And as for me... my essence is bound to this place. I cannot leave with you.
b9_dialogo_victoria_14: But you still can. Let me use what remains of my echo to open a portal.
b9_dialogo_victoria_15: Just... forgive me... I misjudged you. I doubted your intentions until the very end.
b9_dialogo_victoria_16: But now, go, heroes! Leave this dying dream behind.
b9_dialogo_victoria_3: Aphofis' suffering... And these warriors' rage...
b9_dialogo_victoria_4: Let them carve into your cursed body...
b9_dialogo_victoria_6: §cPerhaps you have won, but this place will soon collapse and become your tomb!
b9_dialogo_victoria_7: Maybe for me, but not for these heroes!
b9_info_eothar_0: Maraw'Thar is about to break free, and the power rising within him eclipses even the Conqueror's. Prepare yourselves, your §ctoughest battle§f is coming; you've never faced anything like this.
b9_info_eothar_10:
§b§lMobility (! Important)

§fHaving good mobility and §cteleportation items§f is essential to get out of certain situations! Such as the §dTome of Regression§f, §dEo'thar's Scepter§f, or the §dOmegatrident§f! Speak with Koros' memories in the sanctuary to obtain a §dTome of Regression§f.

§c§lTime Echoes (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§fSometimes Maraw'Thar will leave echoes of your past selves along your path. If an echo takes damage, §cyou take it as well§f!
b9_info_eothar_12:
§c§lEnrage (§c☠§c§l deadly)

§fIf you haven't defeated the boss at the end of phase III, it will §cenrage§f, §cwiping all players out§f with unblockable attacks. §eOptimize your DPS§f!
b9_info_eothar_14:
§e§lThe Final Challenge 

§fThis boss is §c§lVERY DIFFICULT§f. It isn't meant to be defeated on the first try, but rather to be §emastered through learning its patterns§f. Don't worry if it takes you several attempts, this is the §afinal challenge§f of §5§oFinal Paradox§f!

§7(Given the difficulty of the boss, it is §erecommended to play it solo§7 for better concentration. The boss is §bvery fast§7, and a §egood connection§7 is required to fight it in §emultiplayer§7!)
b9_info_eothar_16:
§b§lPoint of View (! Important)

§fIt is recommended to play this boss fight in §ethird-person view§f (F5). The boss moves very fast and having a wider point of view will help a lot.
b9_info_eothar_17: There isn't much time, so I'll be brief. The Conqueror gained his temporal powers by subjugating §eAphofis§f, the great cosmic serpent, using the knowledge of the §eClocktower§f. The suffering inflicted upon §eAphofis§f was so immense that it gave birth to a temporal nightmare within its mind: §cMaraw'thar§f, a being that embodies suffering itself, and feeds on it.
b9_info_eothar_19: The Conqueror was never truly aware that the real source of his power, and the dark flame with which he planned to purge the galaxy, came directly from §cMaraw'thar§f, not from §eAphofis§f.
b9_info_eothar_2: §e▶ §7Wait. Can you explain me what is happening?
b9_info_eothar_21: Now §eAphofis§f is tormented by this nightmare, which is on the verge of becoming real, and unstoppable, unless we stop it right now! Our chances are slim, and I hate to say it, but you are the only silver bullet capable of ending this being.
b9_info_eothar_22: §e▶ §7Why don't you consider us §eheroes§7? Have we done something wrong?
b9_info_eothar_23: By §edefeating the Conqueror§f, you have completely §cfreed Maraw'Thar§f. And now, on top of everything, he wields the power of the cosmic cores within the Conqueror's own body... The situation is desperate. It would have been better if you hadn't played at being heroes and meddled with the timelines! A future with Thar Kroo as leader would have been a paradise compared to what awaits us if this being gets his way. You want to be §eheroes§f? §eThen prove it now§f.
b9_info_eothar_24:
Are you sure you want to start the fight? 
§4§l<!> WARNING <!> §r§cThis boss is tough. It is highly §erecommended§c that you §eread the tips §cbeforehand. §7§o(They are very brief)

§b§lEo'Thar Help (! Important)

§fEo'Thar is greatly weakened, but with her last breath she will grant you §c§lStrength IV§f for the entire encounter. §eUse your sword§f to maximize DPS! Bows and other weapons are not as effective.
b9_info_eothar_3: Unfortunately, I cannot anticipate his moves, only offer some §ebrief§f advice. You're going in §cblind§f to the abilities he'll use.
b9_info_eothar_9:
§b§lAtacrom's Gauntlet (! Important)

§f- Maraw'Thar's attacks deal §cmassive damage§f that §ebreaks§f through any §eimmunity§f or §eresistance§f, but you can §aparry§f them using the §dGauntlet of Atacrom§f! 

- §eYou don't need to eat§f to §dregenerate ❤§f, the gauntlet gives you §esaturation§f for every parry!! 

- Block intelligently, §emissing a parry§f leaves you §cvulnerable§f while the cooldown recovers.

- Make sure §c§leveryone§f has a gauntlet, or speak with Atacrom again at the forge.

§c§lIMPORTANT:§f The attacks that are §b§lBLUE§f in color are infused with primordial dark fire. They §c§lcannot be blocked§f, only §adodged§f!

I don't know... She's far too young to meet the same fate as Bani, and if she does, the consequences could be catastrophic. Go to Aphofis, §etake one of her scales§f, and show it to every doctor you can find. We're running out of time...

§fIf this plan fails... everything you have fought for until now could have been in vain. Good luck, heroes

cld_lore_109: §e... §7§o(Your hand starts §ehurting intensely§7, and you feel a §esupernatural force§7 getting in the way.)
cld_lore_111: §e... §7§o(You feel that instead of absorbing the nightmare, the §cnightmare has begun to absorb you§7.)
cld_lore_112: §e▶ §7The pain is unbearable now, but you choose to endure bravely!
cld_lore_113: §eARGWGGRGRR!! §7§o(You're on the verge of collapsing, you can't endure any longer. You feel your body §csuccumb§7 to the §cnightmare§7 as it §cpulls§7 you toward an §cunknown place§7.)
cld_lore_117: §cAdvancing without fear, straight into the wolf's maw...
cld_lore_118: §cI await you at the end of this hall... impatiently... §oMwahahaha!

cld_lore_124: §e... §7§o(Aphofis turns her head and looks at you gratefully and happily)
cld_lore_127: §e▶ §7No chains bind you anymore, Aphofis. Your legend will endure!
cld_lore_13:
§eMaraw... Thar... §8§o(You have received an Aphofis scale in your inventory)


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fLook for clues in the §e§nscale item that is in your inventory§f and figure out who you should take it to.
cld_lore_130: Phew... that was a relief. I worried too much when I saw how the nightmare absorbed you as you placed your hand on Aphofis.
cld_lore_132: I'm glad you're in one piece! And I'm glad Aphofis is safe and sound... at last! You should probably §etalk to Aphofis§f, I think she is §egrateful§f to you.
cld_lore_134: §a▶ Maraw'Thar has fallen. Your sister... vanished along with the nightmare. She said she loved you.
cld_lore_135: I assumed that when the nightmare disappeared, my sister would fade away as well... It is hard. I will miss her, but I will remember her courage and sacrifice forever.
cld_lore_137: I will also remember your valor, heroes. Once again, you emerge victorious from the most terrifying situations.
cld_lore_139: Meanwhile, I will keep trying to find a new purpose... now that my vengeance for my sister and for the galaxy has been fulfilled.
cld_lore_14: §e▶ §7I don't think I understood you Aphofis... but I'll find a doctor!
cld_lore_141: By the way... you should go and see how §eAphofis§f is doing.
cld_lore_143: §a▶ In the end, I went to check on how Aphofis was doing.
cld_lore_144: How did it go? I've taken so much advantage of the Conqueror's absence from my trade routes that I could barely keep up with you.
cld_lore_145: §e▶ §7Don't worry, it's normal you didn't even notice... it was nothing.
cld_lore_146: From the way you say that, I'm not sure whether I'd rather know more or stay blissfully ignorant...
cld_lore_147: §e▶ §7I only had to defeat what, until recently, was the most powerful entity in the galaxy...
cld_lore_148: I expected nothing less from the heroes of this galaxy. Safeguarding the integrity of my business once again. And now that the galaxy is out of danger... what will you do?
cld_lore_149: §e▶ §7I think I'll take some loooong vacations.
cld_lore_150: That sounds good. Rest is important... I should probably take a break as well...
cld_lore_153: So, would you like to keep listening to the §esanctuary§f music? §7§o(This option only affects the sanctuary. The map's general music volume is controlled via Jukebox/Noteblocks volume slider; don't set it to 0 or you'll miss the music from cinematics and bosses).

cld_lore_16: §eDark stygia§9 oozes from the scale. You may not
cld_lore_161: §e▶ §7Wait, But I §ealready defeated Maraw'Thar§7 with your sister's help!
cld_lore_17: §9know any doctors, but you do know a §eblacksmith
cld_lore_21: What do you have there? That's disgusting, it's covered in dark Stygia and slime. Where did you get this, and why are you bringing it to me?
cld_lore_22: §e▶ §7It's a scale from §eAphofis§7. She's very sick.
cld_lore_23: From §eAphofis§f? Is she contaminated? This could be very serious...
cld_lore_25: Damn... §8§o(He pauses, eyes fixed on the scale)§f The Stygian energy clinging to this... it is §eprimordial Stygia§f. The Conqueror wielded a refined version, one Éctron shaped and perfected... but this, this is §eraw Stygia§f, born from the §every source§f itself.
cld_lore_26: §e▶ §7We'll have to look for the §esource§7, right?
cld_lore_27: The origin of the Conqueror's power... everything began in the §eclocktower§f of §cHorror's Zenith§f, when the Conqueror stole its secrets to enslave §eAphofis§f... and, as if that wasn't enough, he made sure my sister §eEo'Thar§f didn't survive the events.
cld_lore_28: §e▶ §7Do you think I should go back and §einvestigate there§7?
cld_lore_29: Yes, you must investigate that place. I still can't believe that my sister, as powerful as she was, fell to the temporal nightmare you defeated without even breaking a sweat... §eSomething else is going on§f here...
cld_lore_3:
§7I am not sure. We'd need to take a closer look at the situation, but we really don't want to get too close to that creature. It seems to have contracted some kind of fever or something nasty. You'll have to go yourself and ask a local about it, maybe that §bZachaia§7. 


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fTalk to Zachaia in Serpent Corpse.
cld_lore_30: §e▶ §7But what do I do once I'm there?
cld_lore_31:
My sister wouldn't like this at all, but if you §edestabilize §fthe §eclocktower§f a little, we might be able to §cuncover§f something more... Try §esetting an impossible time§f, one that goes §ebeyond §fthe clock's §e12 hours§f. 


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fGo to §cHorror's Zenith§f, destabilize the clocktower by setting a time §ehigher than 12§f, and investigate what happens.
cld_lore_34: Check your §einventory§f. I've left you some §enotes§f. Just follow the steps.
cld_lore_35: §c▶ §c§l[§e§l!§c§l] §eI defeated Maraw'Thar with your sister's help,
cld_lore_36: Wait... My sister... is she still alive? How? That shouldn't be possible...
cld_lore_37: §e▶ §7Overloading the clocktower opened a portal into Aphofis's dream. We fought the temporal nightmare again before it §efled§7.
cld_lore_38: I see... The clocktower has always been a nexus tied to Aphofis's temporal powers... By destabilizing it, I think you were able to enter Aphofis's dream and witness what is happening... just like my sister.
cld_lore_40: My theory is that Maraw'Thar is a nightmare creature, one born and fed by the suffering of others, in this case Aphofis. It likely existed dormant in her mind long before §eBani§f was ever reborn as her, but the mental torment the Conqueror inflicted to control her powers must have awakened Maraw'Thar... and that has left Aphofis seriously ill.
cld_lore_41: §e▶ §7Eo'Thar said we shouldn't let it manifest in reality again. What did she mean?
cld_lore_42: Maraw'Thar is now likely searching for every possible way to §eleak into reality§f, gain power, and §ekill Aphofis§f so it can fully manifest in our world.
cld_lore_44: One nexus it could leak through was the clocktower. Another... I fear, is the §elifeless body of Thar Kroo§f, the Conqueror, who wielded Aphofis's powers.
cld_lore_45: §e▶ §7Are you serious? His §ebody§7 is right in front of the §5monument§7.
cld_lore_46:
Heroes, you must head to the monument at once! If Maraw'Thar gains access to the Cosmic Cores, I guarantee it will be the end.  


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fGo to the §5Cosmic Monument§f and investigate.
cld_lore_50: §cDo you feel the anxiety and fear in the air, §oheroes§c?
cld_lore_51: §cYou were clever to seek me out here.
cld_lore_52: §cYou may §enot see me§c, but I stand §eso near§c that I can smell your fear.
cld_lore_53: §eThe Conqueror's §cbody is an §eanchor§c bound to the power of §eAphofis§c.
cld_lore_54: §cThrough that anchor, my presence leaks across the veil of dreams.
cld_lore_55: §cAnd though I have not yet regained the strength to manifest physically...
cld_lore_56: §cI am within reach of reclaiming that §epower§c!
cld_lore_6: Yeah... After your victory over Thar Kroo the Conqueror, §eAphofis§f has returned to his home here in Serpent Corpse. But she's not doing well.
cld_lore_60: §cTo abandon Thar Kroo's body in this place...
cld_lore_61: §cTo gift me victory without even realizing it!
cld_lore_63: §cI shall §eclaim§c this §ebody§c, and this §ecosmic core§c myself!
cld_lore_64: §cWith this power, §eAphofis§c will fall... and the §l§4Nightmare§c shall awaken!
cld_lore_66: §fGet over here and §etalk to me right§f now! This situation is spiraling completely out of our control!
cld_lore_68: §e... §8§o(The nightmare has sunk so deep into his mind that Aphofis no longer responds.)
cld_lore_7: §e▶ §7But what's wrong with her? Is she sick?
cld_lore_70: No... I don't know what happened. He was fine a moment ago, and she collapsed...
cld_lore_72: She's not responding anymore, and his gaze is §ecompletely blank§f! She needs a doctor urgently!
cld_lore_73: §e▶ §7This must be the work of §eMaraw'Thar§7 with the power of the §ecosmic cores§7...
cld_lore_74:
But what are you talking about?! Go get help... run!! 


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fGo back to Atacrom and explain the situation.
cld_lore_75: §c▶ §c§l[§e§l!§c§l] §eMaraw'Thar has stolen ALL THE COSMIC CORES!!
cld_lore_76: I know! I know!!! I'm trying to think of a solution...
cld_lore_78: We... We don't know how much time we have until its next move... maybe you should go to Serpent Corpse again and see how the situation is there...
cld_lore_8: I couldn't tell you... but it seems the Conqueror put her through such torment that it has made her seriously ill. She's suffering from a §efever§f, one similar to the one that killed her predecessor, §eBani§f. But this time it looks even worse.
cld_lore_80:
That will give us an estimate of how quickly and desperately we need to act. 


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fGo back to §3Serpent Corpse §fand ask §dZachaia§f about §eAphofis's§f condition.
cld_lore_82: §c▶ §c§l[§e§l!§c§l] §eAphofis is dying... She's not going to make it.
cld_lore_83: The situation is §edesperate§f... With so little time, only one idea comes to mind, and I'm not even sure it will work.
cld_lore_85: When the Conqueror destroyed my body using dark fire, Koros was able to create this armor, which absorbed the remnants of my body and mind, now turned into stygia.
cld_lore_87: If I were to forge a §enew piece§f of similar armor, perhaps we could also §esiphon the nightmare stygia§f from §eAphofis's§f body and contain it.
cld_lore_89: I will forge a gauntlet for each one of you heroes!
cld_lore_9: §e▶ §7Is there anything that can be done for her?
cld_lore_91: Wait a moment, I'm §cbusy forging§f right now!
cld_lore_92:
§fI've forged a gauntlet §efor each of you§f. Distribute them among yourselves and speak to me again! 


    §a§l[§e§l!§a§l] §e§lObjective: §fTalk to Atacrom about the next step.

cld_lore_98: §fGo to §eAphofis§f once more, and place your hand upon them so the gauntlet can §edrain the nightmare§f.

luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b2.dialogo: §4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Koros... we have failed. The universe is doomed... Because of me.
I'm sorry, Creator.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Very well...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You shall feel the heat of a thousand stars!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Very smart!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c But is it enough?
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I see I wasn't underestimating you.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Get ready!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c It is over!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Prove to me I'm not mistaken with you!
Warning! In this phase Thar Kroo will cast §6Flaming Field§f §ctwice§f as many times!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c It's the moment of truth!
Fire will soon spread! Seek for a safe place among the flames!
Thar Kroo... My creator... He sacrificed to grant us the §cred core§f, and his §epower§f...
The Conqueror §ewill not§f be able to §edominate§f your minds!
We cannot fail now, you are the only spark of hope that exists.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Enough!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Guide them to a better future.
I will not mistake you... Creator.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You have surpassed all my challenges.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I know you're worthy, and I trust you with the future of the galaxy.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c When you complete the monument with the cosmic cores, you will be able to travel to §oParadox Citadel§r§c.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You will be on his territory, and I... won't be able to come with you.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c He can dominate your minds, but I shall grant you a fragment of me to resist his control.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I hope that, in name of peace, my sacrifice shan't be in vain!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I hope that all lives I destroyed can forgive me.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Koros... you have guided them here...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You have finally arrived.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Invasions, Blackfire... However, the worst would come later.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c After stealing knowledge from §eEo'thar§c, dominating §eAphofis§c and reuniting all §eCosmic Cores§c I learnt how to §etravel in time§c.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c With this power I became invincible and reached my revenge.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I unified galaxy and obtained peace... Or so I thought.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c With time, I noticed that my own society was a ruthless empire.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c And in the end... I annihilated everything.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Full of regret, I traveled to the past seeking heroes that could right my wrongs.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c You shall be who stop my younger self in your present, before he dominates §eAphofis§c and completes the first travel in time.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Otherwise, it shall be too late.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I've been waiting for a long time.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c But first...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Face me!
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c And prove to me you are strong enough to receive my power!
Talk to me before facing Thar Kroo! There are things you must know...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c And know you shall know the truth...
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I... am §lThe Conqueror§r§c.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Or at least, I used to.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c Years ago, when I was young, they conquered my natal world, killing nigh all members of my species.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c That very day I swore to seek revenge.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c I would conquer and bring peace to this galaxy, so that no one else ever had to suffer what my species suffered.
§4§o§l<Thar Kroo>§c My methods were detestable, as you have seen. I was sure the end would justify the means.

luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b3.dialogo: §6§o§l<Ectron> §eW-who will continue my research if I'm gone?
Good job, heroes. I was very worried when the Conqueror appeared.
You've been witness of a fragment of his power... And he almost destroys you...
There is much more fighting up ahead...
Talk to me before facing Ectron! I know how you can beat him.
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eThe experiment has been a total success!§c
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eSoon even the Conqueror will pale in comparison to my power!§c
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eCome close! It won't hurt! I promise...§c
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eI will scorch your flesh, until you're nothing but embers!§c
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eLet's see how you fare against these toys!§c
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eIt is time to carbonize these lab rats!
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eWell! Seems like the lab rats do know how to run!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cBehold how they shrivel with my mere presence!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cFaithless... Vulnerable... You hold no chance whatsoever.
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cAnd yet... You allow them to remain alive because you are §lWEAK§c!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cYou cannot be entrusted with my holy task any longer!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cYou are a danger, letting this betrayers of peace triumph!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cI leave you at their mercy!
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eNo... No!! Please don't leave me here!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cYou shall receive your just punishment!
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eI beg you on my knees! Don't leave me with these monsters!
§6§o§l<Ectron> §eI've always served you! Why do you do this now?!
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cEctron... It's embarrasing, that I must come to your aid...
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cPeace is the most noble of causes, and your weak minds cannot grasp it.
§4§o§l<The Conqueror> §cThat is why you deserve to be squashed like worms!
§cWhile I have energy from the towers... I'm invincible!

luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b4.dialogo: Get under my shield or you won't make it!
<Thar Kroo>
This is your last chance!
§cYour end is inevitable!
§aHelp Koros!
§cWhy do you insist on protecting them, Eternal?
§cWhy do you stand in the path of peace?!
§cWhy are you on their side and not MINE?!
§cYou aren't worthy of its legacy!
§cDISAPPEAR!!
§cDo not resist!
I don't know how long I can resist!
Warriors, help me! Thar Kroo has lowered his guard!
His power increases... Keep attacking!
§cYOU...
§cSHALL NOT DEFEAT ME!!!
The Conqueror is weak! Continue!
You shall fall, Thar Kroo!
§cI SHALL NOT!
§cI SHALL BRING PEACE!
§c§lI!
§c§lAM!!
§c§lPEACE!!!
§c§lITSELF!!!!
§cAnd thus is how fate always favors heroes...
§cYou cannot change the fate of the galaxy. You never could!
§cMy job here is done.
§cAphofis!
§cMarch to the §dCosmic Monument§c!
§cAnd it prevents villains like you from triumphing.
§cOnce more, I am granted victory against savages like you.
§cI am the chosen!
§cThe core of an Eternal... In my hands... Finally.
§cAll thanks to your honorable sacrifice!
§cThe location of the §dCosmic Monument§c lies in it.
§cWith the §dCosmic Cores§c and §eAphofis§c under my control...
§cMy power over §etime§c shall be total!
§cMy army is infinite.
§cYou could fight until exhaustion without my troops ending!
§cSurrender now, and I shall grant you a quick and clean death!
Not this time, Thar Kroo!
§4§l<Thar Kroo> §cInteresting...
§4§l<Thar Kroo> §cLong ago I admired your species, little Eternal...
§4§l<Thar Kroo> §cBut peace can only be achieved through war!
§cGet away!
Don't... let... him...
§cPoor Eternal! You cannot run anymore! Accept your fate!
My power is dissipating!
My power has dissipated! Survive as long as you can!
Resist! Prove to Thar Kroo that his army can be beaten!
§cBehold how my infinite army sends you to oblivion!
Heroes, I've granted you a part of my power! End with as many as you can before it dissipates!
§cI must admit my future self has suprised me.
§cI never thought worms like you could even harm me!
§cYour determination and dexterity is admirable...
§cHowever... This is but the beginning.
§cI can still recover my strength and close my wounds.
§cCan't you see!? You hold no chance!
§cAnd now... Accept your tragic end!
Stand under my shield or you won't make it!
§cStand before me, warriors!
§cBut I think you shan't surrender...
§cSo let's end this once and for all!
§cPrepare everything you have, as it will be your end!
Talk to me before facing the Conqueror! There are things you must know...
§cYou arrive here, sent on his behalf...
§cI should tell you, you know not the entire truth...
§cYou're not the first ones...
§cYou're but another sacrifice in the list of pawns sent by him!
§cHe sacrificed before you, and told you of your ''Glorious purpose''
§cYes... I know that story. It has happened countless times...
§cAnd it always has the same end.
§cHe continues to send corpses in the making!
§cAnother pathetic attempt from my future self...
§cConquest is inevitable!
luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b4.h2.msg_: I am §enot chained§f, break yours first!
luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b4.h7.alca: Don't leave the limits of the fight!
luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b4.koros_v: I won't be able to take much more damage!
My structure has been damage! Don't let Thar Kroo hit me!
luisb1202.functions.bossfight.b5.dialogo: What do you think of this!?
§cThese arrows are infused with deadly dragon poison!
§cMove, Koyomi! Don't make me waste arrows!
§cThis shall be the last time you take my bounty!
§cYou can take the core... But the next time, I won't be leaving empty-handed.
You've proven to be tough. You're worthy of the core as a reward.
We'll met in the future, adventurers.
§cI think... we can reach an agreement.
Listen Gariheuz, they didn't give us a break. We're exhausted!
It's fair for them to take it this time.
§cAfter all we've been through to get here? Forget it!
You know they're stronger than us both.
The sooner you accept it, the sooner we can go search some other treasure.
Perhaps it'd be better to negotiate. No?
§cIt's impossible to negotiate with people like them!
Only those affected with §5purple poison§f, can see where the §ctrident rain§f will fall!
§cTime passes... Like poison courses through your veins!
§cVery clever! You've escaped the illusion... For now.
§cIt's time to put these idiots to rest!
§cFeel how poison courses through you and changes reality!
I'll teach them the core belongs to us!
I'll crush them with my trident, Gariheuz!
Let's see how you like this!
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c Alright, alright! Stop, stop! White flag!
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c But listen! Make no mistake. We don't work for him, nor did we give it to him willingly.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c §eThe Conqueror§c is absurdly powerful. Had we not followed his orders, he probably would have reduced us both to styxian essence...
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c Like everyone who tried betraying him...
Adventurers! The core is all yours.
Gariheuz and I shall part in search of new adventures and challenges.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c It's hard to admit, but... I'm glad I faced you. I never expected to feel the adrenaline and excitement of adventure in a defeat.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c Good luck in your adventure... You'll need it.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz> §8(Panting)§c You really are tough... I admit it... but... we're not done yet.
Gariheuz, they've proven to have guts. It's fair for them to take the core. We've lost.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c Are you kidding? After all we've fought to get here!
Stop being so stubborn! They're impressive in combat. They've earned more than our respect.
§o§l<Echo of Koros>§f Who did you give §eAphofis§f to!?
You won't enjoy hearing this, but... Sadly, we had no other choice.
Very important personal things that are none of your business!
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c Very well. Let us decide fairly. §eLet's fight§c for the §3Cyan Cosmic Core§c right here, like true adventurers.
§o§l<Echo of Koros>§f You have no idea of what the stakes are.
Rules are rules... There are no such things as heroes in this galaxy.
§o§l<Echo of Koros>§f Heroes, talk to me before facing the bountyhunters. I know how to defeat them.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c It seems we meet again, adventurers.
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c I suppose you've had un fighting those horrible mosquitoes, but...
This is our bounty. We got here first!
§o§l<Echo of Koros>§f That is unfair! We opened up the path!
§4§o§l<Gariheuz>§c And I captured the cosmic dragon-snake that would have ripped your head right off!

<Notes from Eo'Thar>

§fThe §cred hand§f from the clock tower §erepresents§f the §epresent time§f. Thanks to §dpillars§f, like the one in front of us, we can §emove it§f, which implies §etime travelling§f to the new time. The §enumber§f on top of the §dpillar§f is§f the position to which the §cred hand§f will move when you §eactivate it§f.

 For example, this one would move the §cred hand§f to I. §cYou cannot§f activate a §dpillar§f if the current time is that of the pillar.

§fGreetings, apprentice! Allow me to introduce myself... I am Eo, the warden of the §eClocktower§f. As you know, the tower was built over an anomalous and sacred terrain able to alter time around it. For years, we've been researching its secrets and protecting them from those who wish to make irreverent use of time travel. Defending and respecting the laws of causality is my duty, and shall be yours too in the future. I've left an §3§lEpochwalker§f by your §ewindow§f, and several §enotes scattered around the village§f so you can start your §epilgrimage§f through time using the §dpillars§f.

§fThough not all the refugees of our species arrived here after the invasion of our home, the §9§lHeavenly Citadel§f, truth is it was quite lucky to find this place and stay here. After storing the cosmic core in a safe place, we researched the mystic temporal secrets that this exotic land hides. I doubt there's a place with properties like these in the entire galaxy. 

 From here, you have incredible views of the §eClocktower§f, the structure we built in order to better understand the temporal phenomena that occur here, and that nowadays take many of our species to travel here. With the §cred hand§f we control the §cpresent§f, and the §3blue one§f controls §3what is beyond our present§f.
§fTo all guards who read this note; Please meet as soon as possible inside the house with the §eX seal§f, there is a §l§cvery important §r emergency to discuss.

§fThe parts of the §dpillars§f must be alligned and fit to the milimiter. That's why all pieces where forged by §6my brother§f, only he could manage. The §eeye§f of the §dpillar§f must be perfectly callibrated to that when §e§lall§e apprentices§f §e§llook at it§f while §e§lsneaking§f, the §dpillar§f may§e activativate§f.

The §cred hand§f of the §eClocktower§f indicates the current time. However, the function of its counterpart, the §3blue hand§f, is unique and quite intriguing. If the §3blue hand§f points towards III, an echo of yourself will appear in the present, reflecting the last action you undertook at III. This proves highly useful to §eactivate two §dpillars§e simultaneously§f and §eaccumulate their time§f, since it always captures the final action you took prior to time-shifting.

To illustrate with an example: if it's currently III and I activate the §dpillar I§f, the time shifts to I. If I then employ the §3§lEpochwalker§f to set the §3blue hand§f to III, I will bring forth the version of myself from III who was activating the §dpillar I§f. As a result, if I were to then activate the §dpillar III§f, the §dpillar I§f would also get activated simultaneously, as my echo would be activating it in unison with me, thereby transitioning to §eIV§f.§7 (I+III)

§fMany apprentices forget that §eit's possible to add§f the hour of the §esame pillar twice§f. For example, you could §etravel§f to §eVI§f if §eyou activate twice§f §dpillar III§f using the §3§lEpochwalker§f.

§fThough we never discovered how to travel thorugh time beyond the 12 hour margin that the Clocktower allows, we could find out. However, our moral code strictly forbids it. Imagine what someone able to travel through time with complete freedom could do, without the protection of the Clocktower. Who knows what terrible anomalies and paradoxes could appear.

§fIn one of our trips using the §dpillars§f we discovered a §every useful anomaly§f. Much like time, which is an §eassymetric§f dimension, we observed that §dpillars§f also provide some §eassymetry§f that we can §euse§f to §etravel to new times§f. §fYou've overloaded the console! The ship §eno no longer has a forcefield§f, §eeveryone§f can §eenter§f. Now §etry to overload§f the console §efrom within§f!
§cThis is not over yet! I still have §l§e2 ships§c!
§cNo! You won't get away with this!
§fA repulsive forcefield §cprevents§f you from §cnearing§f the ships. §eEnd§f §eall the turrets§f while I find out how to destroy it!
§fA repulsive forcefield §cprevents§f you from §cnearing§f the ships. §eGo through§f 8 §erings§f to §bbecome overloaded§f. Once §boverloaded§f get into the §einterior of the ship quickly§f!
§fA repulsive forcefield §cprevents§f you from §cnearing§f the ships. §eTalk to me§f to learn how to avoid it!
§fIt seems §eVilktor§f had taken the §aLime Cosmic Core§f in one of the ships that attacked us.
§fCareul! §eSnipers§f have ambushed you! §eTake cover§f from their shots!
luisb1202.functions.carga_lanas.nexo.msg: Return here when you've found the §lWhite Cosmic Core§f in the previous area, §oGlacial Fort§f.
<Maldini>
Welcome to my humble home, adventurer. I live here since I had to leave my old house, in the §eGlacial Fort§f.
§e▶ §7Why did you abandon it?
§eThe Conqueror§f's attack affected the climate, turning it into an unhospitable, frozen place. Luckily, thanks to my magic boots, I could escape the winter.
§e▶ §7Well...

Sadly, I lost §e9 of my cats§f along the way here. If you manage to do it, I will §ereward§f you with my §dboots§f! When you see one, throw one of my §3pocket portals§f at it to bring it back here. 

§2§l[QUEST]:§7 Find Maldini's §e9 cats§7, there are 3 in each area of this intersection. When you see them, §ethrow§7 a §3Maldini pocket portal§7 at them to bring them back.
Don't let the cold catch you!
Oh! Hi!
See you soon.
Not bad. You still got lots to prove, though. Show me it wasn't dumb luck, and bring me the other two beast heads!
§e▶ §7Give §2wild beast§7 head.

Surprising... I may have underestimated you. Your energy reminds me to an old adventurer, friend of mine. You can take his old trident as a reward. I... no longer need it, and I don't think he does, either. You are still lacking one more wild beast, though!
§e▶ §7Give §2wild beast§7 head and collect reward.

Well! You've exceeded all my expectations. I sincerely didn't think you'd make it past the first beast. You're not bad at this, despite looking like rookies. You've earnt my respect, adventurers. I am a man of my word. Take one of the treasures I found in my last journey through Shaar.
Good job... I hope to see you soon.
Good job... Here you go!
§a§l+ §aReceived: §rBeta-Trident
§a§l+ §aReceived: §rEmblem: Millenary Foundry
Where did you say you had the heart of the beast?
§e▶ §7Oops! Must have fallen while we chatted.

I quite missed the adrenaline and emotion of a good fight... On the one hand, you made me feel the old times, and on the other, I'm embarrased to have lost... against you. Good luck in your suicide mission to stop §eThe Conqueror§f.
§e▶ §7I hope I can.
You did it... it's... Impressive! Without a doubt, you're the best heroes of this galaxy. You've earnt all of my respect and admiration. The galaxy and Aphofis are free at last.
§e▶ §7See you in the future, Gariheuz. Say hi to Koyomi!
What brings you to these ruins, outsiders? Very few adventurers manage to get here.
§e▶ §7Who are you?§7
§e▶ §7Can you remind me who you are?§7
§e▶ §7Can you remind me the quest you gave me?§7
§b▶ §bBNow that you like me better. What's your new objective?
§e▶ §7I §edefeated§7 you in the Temple of Aphofis!
§e▶ §7I defeated §eThe Conqueror§7!
§e▶ §7I have the head of a §2wild beast§7!
Maybe I shouldn't tell you, but... My next objective is to gather all the Cosmic Cores of the galaxy. I know there's one in the same place where I beat Aphofis!
§e▶ §7I'm also after the Cores!
§e▶ §7It's fine... forget it.§7
What?! You too? Why would someone like you want the Cores? Who do you work for?
§e▶ §7I seek the Cores to stop The Conqueror.

I'm gald to hear that, actually. I... had to choose between keeping my life or helping §eThe Conqueror§f. But... What makes you think you can beat him? Not even I can face him! Do you even know the power he wields?
§e▶ §7I learnt the hard way when I met him face to face. I don't even know how I survived.

You're crazy... I don't even know how you could consider fighting him, your chances are... Null! Although I admire your cause, I won't stop searching for the Cores. Nothing tells me that you'll get anywhere. Do know that if our interests collide, I shall not fret to fight you and take the Cosmic Cores from you.
§e▶ §7We'll see about that!
Don't you know me? I'm Gariheuz, one of the greatest, if not the greatest, bountyhunter from this galaxy.
§e▶ §7The greatest bountyhunter? What are you doing here?
§e▶ §7Return.§7
I come seeking adrenaline, new objectives and new challenges. Since my great triumph in draconic lands, adventuring just hasn't felt the same.
§e▶ §7Are you speaking of Bani? What happened?
No, its reincarnation, Aphofis. It was a heroic battle until exhaustion. In the end, the beast fell to me.
§e▶ §7Is that the head you have back there?
No... Aphofis is as big as a mountain, and its roar and wings make the earth tremble. That head is just a representation of it I got from a statue I found.
§e▶§7 Impressive! What's your objective now?§7
Those things are left in secret. And moreso to rookies like you.
Those things are left in secret.
§e▶§7 I understand...§7
§e▶ §7Rookies?!
I never heard from you. What makes you think you're strong enough to survive these lands?
§e▶ §7We'll show you!
Very well. Prove to me I'm wrong and bring me the head of 3 wild beasts... If you can. That way you can become someone, earn my respect, and maybe even a reward.
§e▶ §7I accept!
Let's see if you have what it takes.
This is the quest I gave you to earn my respect.

§7§oObtain the heads of 3 §2wild beasts§7§o and give them to Gariheuz. There is a §2wild beast§7§o in every area of this intersection. You'll recognize the item because of the §2green§7§o color of its name. You will obtain a §ereward§7§o for obtaining 2 heads and a §efinal reward§7§o if you obtain the 3.
§7§o> Get close to talk <
Careful! A §2wild beast§f appeared nearby. End it to §eclaim its head§f.
§f§l§rWild beast §f§detected!
§2§lHead of a Wild Beast
Horned Beast
Eye of the Temporal Nightmare
Wild Berkshire
luisb1202.functions.carga_lanas.obtener_: You've unlocked new talents. Visit me when you can to select a new ability!
luisb1202.functions.forja.atacrom.dialog: You've been to the §eMagma Foundry§f? As you know, during my life I forged weapons for §cThe Conqueror§f in that damned place. Before telling you how to survive, I'd like to §erequest something§f...
§e▶ §7What is it?
§e▶ §7Be back later!

As you know, §cThe Conqueror§f sentenced me to death when I refused to forge weapons for him when I found out his intentions. The breaking point was §eProject Nightfall§f, one of his darkest ambitions. And, recently I found out he §ekilled my sister§f... Well, I've been thinking about §ethe blade§f I told you about...
§e▶ §7Project... Nightfall?

§eProject Nightfall§f, in theory, consisted in creating a legendary and powerful §eblade§f that dominated its wielder's adversaries. Thank §eBani§f I never finished it, but its plans and my old forge remain somewhere in the §eMagma Foundry§f.
§e▶ §7What are you trying to tell me?

We could §efinish the blade§f and use it to defeat §cThe Conqueror§f. If we manage to, he won't be able to do anything about it. The problem is that the §ethree plans of the sword§f are lost in the interior halls, and §ethe forge§f is in the uppermost part of the area.
§e▶ §7I'll help, but... How can I resist within the inner halls?
Stygian gas, eh? The §bRespiration Enchantment§f can help you withstand that contamination. If you want, I can §eenchant your helmets myself§f in exchange for all your levels.

The §efirst plan§f and the §esecond plan§f show you the basic controls of the forge and how to move the runes of the floor. The §ethird plan§f explains how the runes on the floor must be and how to place the parts of the sword. §c§nThe parts of the sword shall appear when the runes of the floor are correct.
§e▶ §7I don't understand the §ethird plan§7.
§e▶ §7I understand...

The §ethird plan§f shows a frontal view of the forge. In the first drawing, you can see the placement of the six runes in the floor. The black marks are their shadows upon being rotated. The three runes in front are lowered, so that the rest can be seen from that perspective.
Hold your helmet in your §emaainhand§f. Be warned you will §close all your levels§f.
§e▶ §7Go ahead!
§e▶ §7Hey, actually... I'll enchant it myself.
There you go!
§e▶ §7I wanted to tell you something...

My old forge... Horrible memories come to mind. But it matters not! Did you get the §eplans §fto prepare the forge? If so, tell me when the §aforge and the sword are§f set and ready! I'm excited to achieve revenge... To avenge §emy sister§f!
§8▶ Show me the third plan.
§e▶ §7How do I interpret the plans, exactly?
§e▶ §7The blade is §aready§7 to be forged!
§e▶ §7Sorry... What plans are you talking about?
§e▶ §7Show me the §efirst plan§7.
§8▶ Show me the first plan.
You haven't found it yet.
§e▶ §7Show me the §esecond plan§7.
§8▶ Show me the second plan.
§e▶ §7Show me the §ethird plan§7.
The forge §cis not ready§f yet. Check the plans.
The forge §cis not ready§f yet. Check the plans and ensure that the §cpieces§f of the sword aren't §c§ntouching each other§f.

Don't you remember? The quest I gave you! In the inner tunnels there are §ethree plans§f that detail how to §eprepare the forge§f to create the blade. I'd do it myself... But I'm not exactly tangible, and I lost most of my memories when I became this armor.
§e▶ §7Ahhh yes! I recall now.
Good idea. Let's get to it.
Quite insightful. Give me some time.
That may work. Wait for a second.
Good enough. Let's try.
Using the forge often exposes your body to the power of the
Stygian Remnants
. For every forged item, you become more exposed, and sometimes you'll obtain §apermanent§f health upgrades.
§e▶ §7Understood, thanks.
What do you have there? The handwriting looks familiar. Give me that!
§e▶ §7There you go.
It can't be! After all this time, my sister... Let me read it.
§e▶ §7Are you Athar'Krom?.
§7§o(While he reads the card, the papers is slowly torn and the shine of his eyes becomes wrathfully intense.)
§e▶ §7A temporal nightmare ended everyone in there... I'm very sorry.

Damned... Damned! §eThe Conqueror§f cares not to end half a galaxy to obtain what he wants... All the time I served him, hiding the fact he killed my own sister... If I had known, I would have forged §ethe damn blade§f he requested... And I would have §estabbed him§f in the chest!
§e▶ §7What are you talking about?
It matters not... It's better for that blade to never see the light of day. But... I will avenge Eo... I swear! I will make him pay for this and suffer for every second that is left of the universe.
§e▶ §7I think the best you could do is channel that wrath to forge weapons that can help us defeat him.

I need to think... Thank you for bringing this here, the last will of my sister. She gave her life to keep the secrets of time and protect the universe from people like The Conqueror. With her, time was safe; With him, who knows what lies in the future... Please take this, as proof of my gratefulness.
§e▶ §7Receive item.
During your journey, you shall obtain
Forge Materials
. Each Forge Material has an §eunique matching item§f. If you manage to get both matching items in this anvil and have 12
Stygian Remnants

in your inventory, I'll be able to forge a §dpowerful item§f, perhaps even a§6 legendary one§f, for you. 

 To place items in the anvil, §edrop them§f nearby.

 Pay attention to the §edetails§f of the Forge Materials to properly match them.
§e▶ §7How do I get Stygian Remnants?
So you made it... My revenge, achieved at last...
§e▶ §7We couldn't have made it without you, Atacrom!
I'm somewhat glad I helped you defeat him, but I wish I could have looked at him in the eye when he died, or that I could have taken his life myself.
§e▶ §7Koros didn't make it out alive.

Nothing shall ever repair the damage that The Conqueror caused, much like nothing can bring back those we lost in the way. My sister... Koros achieved his goals, much like I achieved revenge. I know not my purpose now... I have nothing left. I must think...
§e▶ §7Thank you, Atacrom. Hopefully we'll meet again.
I trust you can use this well.
Well... there you go.
Fixed!
Freshly made!
Not bad. All yours.
Ectron was a good rival, but I make the best weapons.
I'll miss you, sister.
The materials don't match.
Not a good idea.
Impossible. Try something else...
Not going to work. Try again.
Doesn't look good. Any other ideas?
Hey... Where did you get these materials? I forged a very similar one for a young piglin long ago...
You found every item I could forge... I feel my power... returning. Congratulations!
Perhaps one of the mightiest blades I've ever forged. The power of creatures like Koros lies within it.
Perhaps one of the mightiest blades I've ever forged. The power of creatures like Thar Kroo lies within it.
Don't lose your head.
Mind your steps.
Don't get overconfident.
Stay alive.
Careful out there.

luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.con: Yes... my goons already informed me. I'm sorry about your geometric friend... I never met him, I avoided him at all costs... But he undoubtedly took a great part in your victory.

Now that Thar Kroo is no longer in the way, I will be able to expand my business more than ever. Despite the fact that our paths and interests no longer allign, I won't forget the favors I owe you. If you ever run into trouble, you know who to call!
If a friend of yours §cdies§7§o in combat, use the §aSmuggling Tome§7§o on his items to §esend them§7§o quickly to the Sanctuary.
§cStrength§7§o also improves the damage of maces, but with 66% of the regular effect.
The §etome of the conqueror§7§o makes §ehooks§7§o have no cooldown.
You can use §etomes§7 directly §efrom your inventory§7 by pressing the drop button (Q) on them, saving you slots on your §ohotbar§7.
If you §cdie§7§o durante a §eboss fight§7§o it will §erestart§7§o, but you §ewon't lose§7§o your §eitems§7§o and you'll reappear by the entrance.
§eFallen beehives§7§o and §ebees§7§o are not effective against bosses.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.err: Where do you think you're going with a §bSmuggled Chest §7out of here!? Get rid of it before leaving! I don't want anyone to discover me.
The Smuggling Tome has been fully upgraded.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.fac: Lemme see... AHHHGSS!! WHERE DID YOU GET THAT! §8§o(He puts an arm out and tries to take it from you, nervously)
§e▶ §7There's something with MY NAME here, and someone called Mr. Ery. Anything you want to tell me?
No... well, yes, well... Listen. This is for the greater good... which includes you. Give me that and let's forget I put your name next to mine to take... ''economic shortcuts''.

Listen... Give me that piece of paper so that it doesn't see the light of day again. And I expand the services I give to you like the trustworthy fellow you are. Whatcha think? Remember, we have the same enemy, it's beneficial for us both.
§e▶ §7Fine... But you could at least tell me what you're doing my personal information!

There are things that are best left unknown, but, for me it's very important that such information isn't publically known. Before anything, thank you for taking care of that. Here's what I can offer you:

will give you

and you will also recover some of the

luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.fra: My goons could recover §csome§7§o of the §eitems§7§o you lost. Pay me a visit to §erecover them§7§o!
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.giv: How dare you lose such secret things around here willy-knilly! Anyways... here.
§e▶ §7I wanted to tell you something else...
My workers have recovered some items which we think might belong to you.
§e▶ §7 I want to recover lost items.
There you go. Try to have it not happen again.
§e▶ §7Thank you. I wanted to tell you something else...
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.ida: If they ask, you don't know.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.ini: §b▶ Did anything happen to you during the invasion? Are you okay?
§e▶ §7I'd like to §frecover the items§7 from the Smuggling                   Tome.

§b▶ §bI stole an insignia from a bountyhunter!
§b▶ §bI'm going to face The Conqueror. I need help!

§b▶ §bI have something important that might belong to you.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.inv: How could I be fine if anyone can trace you back here! I'm glad you kicked them, I was getting worried watching rocks fall from the ceiling.
§e▶ §7Shh! I don't want Koros to hear you.
Since it's on my best interest that you get away with your plan, I'm going to give you great articles so that you can be ready for anything. Have §e§otwo free slots§r in your inventory.
XP in large quantities and a trusty weapon. Whatcha think? Use them carefully.
Eh! You! Come here! We gotta talk.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.lic: Well well... Looks like the insignia of an old friend. Long time since I head from him, and you bringing me this only confirms that he probably had a bad trip. The premium services that he had bought haven't expired, so... §eguess you can keep them§7§o.

Ehmm... Long story short, it's a pack of services only our wealthier friends may buy. But since our interest allign, I'd have no issue in, you know, forgetting the whoseabouts of the old guy and linking them to you.
I'm sure you'll like them, they're very useful for reckless adventurers like you. Here's what I offer:
your items related to or forged in
your lost items. More valuable items will be
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.nos: Hey... with all the thing with the data leak, the guy from whom I sto... borrowed! the revolver I gave you, is going to "need it" back. I kinda don't want trouble. Could you bring me §4§lDispute§7§o back?
§e▶ §7And you take my weapon? Like that?
No no no! I have... something else! Another luxury product that will come in handy!

Look, I was saving this in case it was time to survive in a dystopian galaxy where The Conqueror ends up controlling everything. But you did beat up the Terrastalkers. And Gariheuz. Maaaaaaybe you can beat him. This will come in handy.
This gun has some... §oinconvenients§7. Quite weird ones. I don't know where my goons got it from, but I doubt it's a problem for you!
Tss! Tss! Come here! Do you still have the revolver I gave you?
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.pri: I saw you fighting and maybe you can help me.
§e▶ §7Who are you and what are you doing here?!!
Shhhh! Drop it! I don't want your geometric friend to find me. It was quite hard to get here to have you yell my location.

Anyways; First thing first, we have several enemies in common, like... The Conqueror. All of 'em are making business hard, with regulations and customs.

 And second things second, you probably found some
We use those precious gems for the creation of all sort of weap-- jewelry. They're very expensive in the black market.
§e▶ §7Alright. What are you giving me then?
, and then we can talk business.
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.seg: A deal's a deal. I'll grant you access to my smuggling network so that you can transport your items to the Sanctuary, no taxes, no customs. Sound good?
you bring me, I'll increase the capacity of the §bSmuggling Tome§r. And one last thing...
You can also use my smuggling network to §eteleport to your friends§r. To not get my workers in danger, you'll only be able to teleport if there are no enemies nearby.
§e▶ §7Ehm... Yes... Well, I left them on a chest... Be right back!
luisb1202.functions.misterio.dialogo.tro: The piglin tyrant fell? Quite surprising... With his empire falling down, we can open new routes without worry. During previous research we found that Apiglo collected swords. Many of them had... peculiar bitemarks. I don't know if it'll help, but you can take one of those, I guess.
§9to eat it. Who would eat a sword?

Well... You did make me a favor. That jerk Ectron was making weapons for The Conqueror non-stop. Without him, my projects are quite safer. By the way... We got some of his tech a while back, by some... well... payment. Grab it, I'm sure it'll come in handy.
Gariheuz's bountyhunter insignia... That's gonna be handy to impersonate him and skip some checks. Y'know. Not long ago we stole some treasures from Gariheuz, maybe they interest you.
And... Where is what you wanted to give me?
The Conqueror from the future sacrificed himself to stop himself? The Conqueror is our common enemy. If what you say is true, I'll help, but I need some proof.

We stole this crystal in a raid to one of The Conqueror's bases. Though it seems like a prototype, maybe it's part of one of the weapons he wants to create.

 Maybe that blacksmith can work with the crystal and turn it into a weapon.

 Good luck with your final battle.

luisb1202.functions.talentos.minikoros.d: Some buildings of this place are §eonly accessible at a given time§f. A temporal cataclysm affected this village long ago. All remains exactly as it was the day of catastrophe, though temporal corruption has reached every place and taken every inhabitant. We must find out more about this place to be able to find the §7§lGray Cosmic Core§f.
Outsiders took this sanctuary long ago and shall fight back, but we have two objectives here: The §9Blue Cosmic Core§f and finding the portal to the §dCosmic Realm§f.
§e▶ §7The Cosmic Realm? Have I been there before?

Exactly, a place where all Cosmic Cores will be able to combine their power and find out where and when is the §d§oParadox Citadel§r, The Conqueror's base of operations. It's impossible you've been there, my maker sealed that portal. But we §emust reopen it§f with the power of the §9Blue Cosmic Core§f.
§e▶ §7How come they haven't used the Core to open the portal yet?
An ancient mechanism hides the Core away. My maker told me that §eonly when all stars gaze towards the Cosmic Core§f, it will be revealed. We have to find out what he meant.

This mystic world, once called the §9§lHeavenly Citadel§f, was the §enative home §fof The Conqueror and his species. Peace in this kingdom lasted for eons, until bloodthirsty outsiders arrived and killed everyone, except him and a couple survivors... It was the beginning of §eThe Conqueror§f's noble motive: Peace. With time, he lost his way, and now he believes peace can only be brought with §cblood§f and §csacrifice§f.
Need me to remind you anything?

Every 3 minutes a meteor shower will fall upon us. It is §cunavoidable§f and goes through all ceilings and walls. The only way to survive is to §eget under my shield§f or use a §etome of invulnerability§f. I will tell you when one arrives and I will §eteleport next to one of you§f when it arrives to protect you. So §estay close§f to be protected!

Some §ecolorful flowers§f that have interesting effects upon being destroyed. Mind that they can §ebenefit§f both §eyou§f and §eenemies§f! I'll be able to tell you their effects once you try them. Come back if you need to check the information!

The citadel that lies here is the result of a surprising cosmic event. Long ago, an alien flower fell onto this asteroid. The flower expanded until it covered everything with an exhuberant, unique vegetation.

A group of survivors from the conquest managed to get here seeking refuge. Since then, they maintain an interesting symbiotic relationship where the rock and its inhabitants take care of each other and fight against intruders.

The climate in this strange meteor is very §cdangerous§f. Now and again, §cdeadly showers§f of stygian meteorites that can annihilate any unprepared outsider will take place. Additionally, you'll quickly become acquinted with the... peculiar §avegetation§f.
§e▶ §7How can I survive the meteor showers?

The §oMakers§f never created the Green Core in fear that someone would gather them all and use their power for evil. That's why we're here, to §ecreate§f ourselves the §aGreen Cosmic Core§f. However, we'll need a §eCosmic Receptacle§f as a base to create the §aGreen Core§f. The §eMegamatrix§f carefully protects these receptacles and let's no one get near.
§e▶ §7Fine. How do I beat the Megamatrix?
Indeed, §eit can stop its bullets§f, but §cnot its missiles§f.

First you need to §6destroy 8 defense matrixes§f before accessing the core of the §eMegamatrix§f. These §6defense matrixes§f summon §cTerrastalkers§f when they feel a threat nearby and are §eimmune§f to all damage. I don't quite know how to destroy these §6defense matrixes§f. You'll have to find out yourselves...
They're deadly siege weapons with four hydraulic-based legs. They have a 70-mm turret and §cmissile launchers§f.

Exactly, they work in a similar manner, but when they run out of bullets they §elaunch a seeking missile§f towards a player. The missile becomes faster and faster and §ewill only stop if it collides with 2 blocks§f. If it hits the player, they take §csevere damage§f and §cALL§f players are §7weakened§f and §7fatigued§f for 10 seconds. This zone is an old laboratory that the §oMakers§f used to create and code the worlds of this universe and create the Cosmic Cores. These two supreme creature disappeared when their creation was done, and left behind a branching defense system to protect this holy place in their absence; §eThe Megamatrix§f.

To open the door to the room where Thar Kroo lies, you'll need to §eenter the main fortress§f and activate the lever in the east wing §7§o(-1283 69 2207)§r, the west wing §7§o(-1650 64 2207)§r§f, and the top zone §7§o(-1523 156 2110)§f.

. You must obtain the §e8 Stygian Keys§f to access the heart of the citadel, where The Conqueror awaits. Be wary of dangers like §cChaining Blades§f and the §cElite Blazes§7!
